cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.CC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses a formalism for programming under a complexity-theoretically motivated type system, which is a topic that falls under the scope of logic in computer science.
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes an extension to the ATR programming formalism, which is a version of call-by-value PCF. This is a topic that falls under the scope of programming languages.
3. cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) - The paper discusses the time-complexity semantics for ATR and shows that the new recursion schemes do not lead out of the realm of feasibility. This is a topic that falls under the scope of theoretical computer science.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses a type system for ATR programs that run in type-2 polynomial-time, which is a topic that falls under the scope of computational complexity.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the ability of the revised ATR to express classic insertion- and selection-sort algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
